article:
'Strong House' or 'Strong Hall' may refer to:

*Strong House (Coventry, Connecticut), listed on the National Register of
Historic Places (NRHP) in Tolland County *Strong-Davis-Rice-George House,
Eatonton, Georgia, listed on the NRHP in Putnam County *Fernand-Strong House,
Lawrence, Kansas, listed on the NRHP in Douglas County *Strong Hall (Lawrence,
Kansas), listed on the NRHP in Douglas County *Strong House (Amherst,
Massachusetts), listed on the NRHP in Hampshire County *Strong's Block, Newton,
Massachusetts, listed on the NRHP in Middlesex County *William Strong House
(Preston, Minnesota), listed on the NRHP in Fillmore County *Rau/Strong House,
St. Paul, Minnesota, listed on the NRHP in Ramsey County *William Strong House
(Spring Valley, Minnesota), listed on the NRHP in Fillmore County *Richard
Strong Cottage, Dublin, New Hampshire, listed on the NRHP in Cheshire County
*Capt. Richard Strong House, Dublin, New Hampshire, listed on the NRHP in
Cheshire County *George A. Strong House, Plainfield, New Jersey, listed on the
NRHP in Union County *Elijah Strong House, Ashland, New York, listed on the
National Register of NRHP in Greene County *Jedediah Strong House, Colonie, New
York, listed on the National Register of NRHP in Albany County *Strong House
(Vassar College), a college dormitory in Poughkeepsie, New York, also known as
Strong Hall *Thomas Strong House, Wainscott, New York, listed on the NRHP in
Suffolk County *John Stoughton Strong House, Strongsville, Ohio, listed on the
